{"_id":"83Sf2PpGCY6529Aa","name":"PoA Tomb of Moving Stone","permission":{"default":0,"UGVR9scTfzwLsmWX":3},"folder":"","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<h3 id=\"T1EntryCavern\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"277b7d87-1641-47ed-a80c-f4afb1411817\">T1. Entry Cavern</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5597659a-d8c7-4b2b-a024-e2c8e979a9d4\">If the sinkhole opened up, this cavern has a pile of dirt in the center and a gaping, 20-foot-diameter hole in the 30-foot-high ceiling.</p>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"045d1c86-a283-4d8a-9598-365192da533b\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"743f80ec-5e41-412e-afca-d124a1e295df\">This wide, irregularly shaped cavern has a floor of smooth bedrock. Damp dirt and stone, with tree roots protruding here and there, make up the walls. A five-foot-wide tunnel leads off to the north, and a stone slab &mdash; a door with a rusty pull-ring &mdash; stands to the east. By the stone door, a couple well-used cloaks and a waterskin are on the floor.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"4a5d6539-e364-4926-8c23-21762fd8656b\">The waterskin is half full of water. The cloaks are quite plain. They belong to Believers who don&rsquo;t want to attract attention while coming or going from the entrance tunnel.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5c4b5463-f921-45e1-b6a4-bfbd05534666\">The stone door to the east has no lock. It slides open smoothly. Beyond it, a passage of dressed stone slopes downward, continuing east to area T2.</p>\n<h4 id=\"NorthTunnel\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16.8px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"99b5249f-9662-4f46-b4b5-29410377f62d\">North Tunnel</h4>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"50c794d5-59a3-4fb0-a3d5-a17ccb2318fa\">This tunnel leads to the Mellikho Stoneworks quarry (Red Larch, area 18). If the characters investigate the tunnel, read the following:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5142ff20-4176-4544-bf3a-28f09ac5fcda\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ac8b5bc0-562d-4f4a-8215-1572d9047c81\">The tunnel is muddy. It winds north a long way before rising gradually. After two hundred feet or so, it ends at a wooden door that forms a sloping roof. A small wooden coffer sits on the floor by the door, and beside the coffer is a heap of damp sand from which the ends of torches protrude.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2d79f735-2881-40bb-a8e8-3d48eec18a77\">Beyond the wooden door, the tunnel continues ten feet before opening into the quarry behind Albaeri Mellikho&rsquo;s house.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"21f487b2-bde4-4796-af7f-f99f6455d27f\">The damp torches were extinguished by being thrust into the sand. They are hard to light but readily burn if lit with an existing fire. The coffer contains flint and steel, as well as six dry torches.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"21f487b2-bde4-4796-af7f-f99f6455d27f\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 id=\"T2StoneSentinels\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c2705f42-7798-46dd-99df-65b5d94576b8\">T2. Stone Sentinels</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ffc15b0f-dce0-486b-8648-e174d97acfd8\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7c362423-907b-43ef-a1e9-e7de34e10013\">Sixty feet beyond the stone door, the tunnel levels out. Two stone reliefs of stern dwarves in chain mail and carrying battleaxes face each other across the tunnel. The carvings stand out from the passage walls, and they have gaps around them, so they could be doors. The passage continues past them.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"0be62d51-21f3-425b-b349-39d3d3a479a0\">The doors slide open easily if pushed. To the south, the door leads to a long stone tunnel that ends in a pit covered by a stone bench with a hole in it (a privy unused for decades). The door on the north side of the hall guards a passage leading to area T5.</p>\n<h3 id=\"T3CageTrap\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"3e853237-2c31-4520-b3b4-1f4e56332c55\">T3. Cage Trap</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"90b2e3c7-e992-49af-ab18-b57e62af6a82\">If the party continues east along the tunnel past area T2, they walk into a trap. Read the following text only if a character examines the ceiling:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e33994fa-6125-4ede-90f3-7a2966427805\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1aaeeccc-c1b6-4f7f-a09d-e9cda8fb5186\">The ceiling consists of square stone panels about ten feet on a side. Rusty iron frames surround each panel. The panels are suspended about several inches from one another and the wall to either side. They form a row overhead that continues down the passage.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"156fb8a9-1532-481f-abdc-a3873fc9b84f\">Ten iron cages are suspended from chains over the hallway, and the &ldquo;panels&rdquo; are the cage bottoms. The true ceiling is 25 feet high, and each cage hangs from 5 feet of heavy chain and is 10 feet tall. The bottom panels appear to be a 10-foot ceiling from the hallway. The panels are thin plaster painted to resemble stone.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7abea20a-893e-4c5d-8bf8-8051486eeb48\">When the characters can see the eastern end of the hall, read the following:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1d55cc49-7a1f-4851-962a-933cbe526f38\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d03a0d45-0105-4a36-9806-6b4ec3172b42\">At the end of the passage is another stone door with an iron pull ring in it. It stands slightly ajar with darkness beyond. About five feet up, the door has a two-inch-wide, foot-long horizontal slit.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"97c1d567-b62c-49f6-8335-386c6c46dee7\">Unless Grund (male half-orc&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Serif plural-monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #bc0f0f; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d309715c-d270-4c3e-99fb-85fd7f3f5e49\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/thug\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17035-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">thug</a></span>) has already been dealt with, he is peering through the viewing slit. With his&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover sense-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/basic-rules/monsters#Darkvision\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/senses/2-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">darkvision</a>, he spots approaching characters 60 feet away, but if the characters are carrying light sources, he notices them as soon as they pass the doors in area T2.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e5a0fdb4-b8f1-40ca-b9cf-0768dd10b13f\">Grund&rsquo;s orders are to trap intruders. Anyone who isn&rsquo;t an intruder is supposed to pause 60 feet from the door, cross his or her fists, and call out, &ldquo;A Believer approaches!&rdquo; Grund drops cages on anyone who doesn&rsquo;t follow this protocol.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"997b808f-7b9f-43d0-a5a6-fdb34aaed761\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9dfbb931-4016-4be6-ba66-cc39f2b3ee46\">Dropping Cages.</span>&nbsp;Each cage&rsquo;s chain runs through a pulley secured to a heavy iron bar just inside the door in area T4. From where he is, Grund can use an action to release two chains. He starts with the cage at the western end of the tunnel, sealing off retreat, followed by a cage dropped on the party. Roll initiative at that point. Grund&rsquo;s uses his second turn to block the eastern edge of the passage with a third cage and to drop another cage on characters not already trapped.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"cfdd309f-e2c4-44c3-b325-589daef46a85\">A falling cage targets the corresponding 10-foot square section of the passage. Targets in the area can stand still, taking no damage as the plaster on the cage bottom breaks and the cage seals them in. Those who wish to avoid a falling cage must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw. Those who fail are caught in the cage. Anyone who fails by 5 or more is hit by the iron frame of the cage bottom. Such a creature takes 7 (2d6) bludgeoning damage and is pinned under the cage. While pinned, the character is&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover condition-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/basic-rules/appendix-a-conditions#Prone\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/conditions/12-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">prone</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover condition-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/basic-rules/appendix-a-conditions#Restrained\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/conditions/13-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">restrained</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"81155154-9cdd-4250-9585-7cc8b1f447e0\">A character who uses an action to make a successful DC 15 Strength check can lift the cage enough to allow one creature to escape. It takes a successful DC 20 Strength check to bend the rusty bars enough to allow everyone in or under the cage to escape. A character pinned under a cage lacks good leverage and has disadvantage on these Strength checks.</p>\n<h4 id=\"Development\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16.8px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"375328e6-3162-4a90-9083-7b8fa9dc6c6d\">Development</h4>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"8f5d87e2-04e0-4e06-9c55-a9f426b8610e\">If Grund traps the characters in the hall, he runs to tell Baragustas in area T8. Baragustas calls the Bringers of Woe (see area T7), who arrive 10 minutes later. The villains raise cages one by one to attack trapped characters, aiming to capture them. Larrakh then plans to sacrifice the characters at a special ceremony.</p>\n<h3 id=\"T4Antechamber\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e5a96d49-8aed-4225-8511-f5ffee1dcbf6\">T4. Antechamber</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d59a7249-b516-43cf-adf8-6b2ad1e8407f\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"41aa8b49-eae0-43e7-957a-491ca7702a3a\">This big, square chamber has been hewn out of the rock. In the center of the chamber&rsquo;s west wall is a stone door that has a narrow viewing slit. Beside the door is a set of iron bars bolted into the wall about three feet above the floor. Ten oiled chains are secured to the bars, leading up to a hole bored in the ceiling. Another solid stone door is in the middle of the east wall.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2f26440e-92a7-4427-a2ba-f46f4dbb2aa9\">An eight-foot-tall rectangular stone stands upright in the room&rsquo;s center. The stone has an inscription on it that&rsquo;s hard to read from a distance. At the foot of the standing stone, a small human is pinned, face down, by rocks placed atop his arms, legs, and back. He is barefoot and wears ragged clothes.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"3654a183-f323-475e-a713-d61d7e693a55\">Depending on what has happened in area T3, Grund (male half-orc&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Serif plural-monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #bc0f0f; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"8b0643e6-4a7c-49ca-9c25-73a19c399332\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/thug\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17035-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">thug</a></span>) might be standing by the western door, keeping watch down the hallway. Grund is baffled by intruders that arrive behind him. After standing and gaping for a moment, he finally says, &ldquo;You can&rsquo;t be here. You have to go!&rdquo; He points down the western hallway. In obvious exasperation and desperation, he attacks anyone who attempts to leave by the eastern door.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"30c37669-3bb0-4e40-a6f3-54e9e74cc0b0\">Pinned under a pile of small boulders is an eleven-year-old boy named Braelen Hatherhand (male Tethyrian human&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Serif plural-monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #bc0f0f; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1cf9ed50-f1e8-4e47-93ba-f3b24d55cc5a\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/commoner\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/16829-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">commoner</a></span>&nbsp;with 2 hit points and no effective attacks). He is drifting in and out of consciousness. If strangers enter the room, he revives enough to feebly plead for his freedom.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body-Last--to-apply-extra-space-\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"da3bb560-2f9b-4564-b504-cde80778aecf\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2a95e35b-f40b-47f9-8463-ef0f14ff9a6b\">Rolelplaying Braelen.&nbsp;</span>Braelen has been pinned here for two days. Heavy stones were carefully placed to hold him in place without crushing or breaking anything. He is cold, thirsty, hungry, tired, and scared. The boy clams up in terror if he&rsquo;s intimidated or bullied. If approached in a friendly manner, he first begs for food and water. He can offer the following information as responses to the characters&rsquo; questions.</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; list-style: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 19.5px; padding: 15px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"21dd44d9-008d-409a-ad0a-2617de9f37d3\">\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ca7cc8df-7f4d-4943-8db9-426390153c5c\">The Believers put him here as punishment for being disobedient. He failed to deliver a message from his father, Rotharr Hatherhand, to Ilmeth Waelvur. It was a slip of paper the boy didn&rsquo;t read.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"a66567ae-3406-41d9-a7a8-2b42da5d2f7c\">Rotharr is one of the Believers. Other Believers Braelen knows are Baragustas Harbuckler, Marlandro Gaelkur, and Ilmeth Waelvur. The boy also knows Grund isn&rsquo;t really a Believer, but the Believers take care of him, so he does what they tell him to do.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"3a222d1a-8adc-4e6e-a1a0-afc8a9b872b1\">The Believers are a secret group made up of some of the most important people in town. They guard the moving stones, and make sure no one disturbs the Delvers, who are entombed here. The Believers watch the moving stones carefully, because it&rsquo;s a bad sign when they move, and they have to figure out what it means to avert danger. (This information isn&rsquo;t true, but that&rsquo;s what the Believers and Braelen believe.)</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d06dfa80-f27c-4b86-a635-e23203d5338e\">Braelen isn&rsquo;t angry with his father or the Believers. He believes this sort of treatment is normal, and he&rsquo;s worried his father might find out the punishment ended before it was supposed to.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted-Last\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"89d453a4-af74-413d-95de-423edffcf2a1\">The chamber of moving stones and the buried Delvers are to the east, beyond three more stone doors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9e17e495-3b59-4d0b-9910-12ef43b5c196\">If the characters release Braelen, he tries to go back to the surface through the tunnel in area T1.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9a154677-2893-48be-90f1-2385a4f5f333\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"bf017c94-b5aa-4bb6-add2-55128f521b4c\">Chains.&nbsp;</span>Fastened to iron bars here are chains to the cages in area T3. Characters can raise a fallen cage back to its original position by hauling on its chain.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"0b85acaa-c60c-4cba-8a74-bb7f33aa7c0a\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"f8cd6f24-f086-4c09-86c0-784bcdf9fd4f\">Inscription.</span>&nbsp;The inscription on the standing stone reads, in Common: &ldquo;Displease not the Delvers.&rdquo;</p>\n<h3 id=\"T5CharnelChamber\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"71b6f72b-5df2-4eaf-8ed3-9724c396acf2\">T5. Charnel Chamber</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d8541e2d-ccd6-48cd-9c04-62ebae647661\">Characters catch the scent of death as they approach this room.</p>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5b241340-d07e-47be-b0a1-6b2818dab63f\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e74100a9-100d-4f12-b3fe-b5432407d10c\">The tunnel opens into a square room that reeks of decaying flesh. Three human corpses, reduced to little more than bloody bone and sinew, are sprawled in the room&rsquo;s center. Two oversized rats root among the bodies, stopping to chew flesh they&rsquo;ve pulled free. Scuttling noises come from narrow crevices in the walls.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"4aa7af13-790e-4526-9241-25fe0654f542\">Five&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Serif plural-monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #bc0f0f; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"fb1040a7-73d2-4cce-b430-a706bda96754\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/giant-rat\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/16891-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">giant rats</a></span>&nbsp;found their way in through the narrow crevices, which are just big enough for the rodents to squeeze through. Two are in the middle of the room, and three more lurk in the crevices. Believers don&rsquo;t yet know the rats are here, and the grisly meal is sufficient to keep the rats from wandering. The giant rats ignore intruders that give them a wide berth and avoid startling them. They attack if harmed or provoked.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"017557b5-0b4b-4f91-9522-e71b7e0be8ea\">The bodies are those of travelers who disappeared near Red Larch. Each has the symbol of the earth cult cut deeply enough in the forehead to mark the skull. To pass a test commanded by the earth cultist Larrakh (see area T9), Believers waylaid and killed the travelers in separate incidents over the last month. The Believers are rarely murderers, but Larrakh is maneuvering them into darker and darker deeds.</p>\n<h3 id=\"T6HoveringStone\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7ee4856f-2e6e-4a67-9c40-57eb43adc0db\">T6. Hovering Stone</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"cdbf188f-3a8e-4f36-9fe0-32a16bad9bcc\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d989901f-5312-4652-8fb5-c987d9a9fdc1\">The tunnel opens into a square room. In the center of it, a black rock about a foot across hovers three feet from the floor.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"165abc4b-c1f0-4fa0-aa6e-2f45a2f343a5\">A normal rock floats here because of ancient magic that maintains an&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover condition-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/basic-rules/appendix-a-conditions#Invisible\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/conditions/8-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">invisible</a>&nbsp;floor-to-ceiling cylinder that is 10 feet wide. Visible to&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"af799eb0-ae6b-47bd-b93e-3622b6263aa3\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover spell-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/detect-magic\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/spells/2065-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">detect magic</a></span>&nbsp;(transmutation school), the column enables objects placed and left in it to float where released. The column can hold up to 500 pounds. Objects in excess of this weight fall. If the characters move the rock, which weighs 20 pounds, out of the column, it is freed from the effect and crashes to the floor.</p>\n<h3 id=\"T7DwarfStatue\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"579a7e78-58bf-4f02-b7e3-85d6da56e067\">T7. Dwarf Statue</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"451628bc-80a9-4537-a23e-32cb7e27d24c\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"421ed2e5-1cb4-4064-b170-eb49555896dc\">This fifty-foot-square chamber is hewn out of rock. The floor is rough but flat, the walls show the chisel-marks of the original builders, and the ceiling is about ten feet high. Identical stone doors with iron pull-ring handles stand in the middle of the east, north, and west walls.<br style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px;\" />In the center of the room stands a life-sized and lifelike statue of a dwarf warrior wearing a chain shirt, helm, and big boots. He carries a shield on his left arm and a battleaxe in his right hand. The statue has clearly been broken into, roughly, the head and upper torso, lower torso, and legs. These pieces have been reassembled and held together and upright in a stout wooden frame. A dagger along with several coins and gems lie on the floor in front of the statue, surrounded by an ring of fine gravel.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body-Last--to-apply-extra-space-\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"69d612d2-0c62-41a3-b7a8-3cde9ce6b513\">The statue is a&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover condition-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/basic-rules/appendix-a-conditions#Petrified\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/conditions/10-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">petrified</a>&nbsp;and long-dead dwarf. On the frame holding it together, a small, neat inscription reads:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"compendium-parchment-blockquote\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; position: relative; width: auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5c2b1cea-fb7a-40e7-97ce-a05094fae242\">\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body ParaOverride-1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"f490409d-d445-4a19-bc8a-274f535676d7\">Petrified Ironstar (?) dwarf,</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body ParaOverride-1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"3103ff88-7f27-4a8f-8ed6-e491ec4c20bf\">found 1459 DR in Red Larch West Quarry</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body-Last--to-apply-extra-space- ParaOverride-1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"0b6ef9c0-3184-4d1b-a823-7a0fca03aac5\">in broken condition.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c42e3d52-4d38-4007-acb3-ab93231e41a0\">The ring of gravel surrounds the statue at a distance of 5 feet, intended to mark a suitably respectful distance from the statue. Believers have a tradition of leaving small valuables here for luck. Larrakh urges them to bring more each tenday so he can collect it and take it with him when he leaves Red Larch.</p>\n<h4 id=\"Treasure\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16.8px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"f2859c80-4026-4399-9d70-afad24dacb1b\"><span class=\"CharOverride-1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"403c47d7-32ba-4277-b416-205f1dbb7dc5\">Treasure</span></h4>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"42ba5711-32e6-4184-9cf4-eeec1a1119fa\">Offerings left here by the Believers include 440 cp, 253 sp, and 97 gp. Six small green agates (worth 5 gp each) and two polished moonstones (worth 50 gp each) are among the coins.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7f686758-814c-4531-8e4d-7d2efb0a30f3\">To encourage the Believers, Larrakh left a&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover magic-item-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/magic-items/dagger-1\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/magic-items/5225-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">+1 dagger</a><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9b5e6c44-b27f-4b65-aaf0-27e3c7080b92\">&nbsp;</span>decorated with star motifs and a grip of night-blue leather. Dried blood still coats the dagger from its use in killing and carving symbols on the murder victims in area T5. The dagger doesn&rsquo;t make noise when it hits or cuts something.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1f5dbdf1-25ec-448c-aeea-6d841cc4c97e\">The name &ldquo;Reszur&rdquo; is graven on the dagger&rsquo;s pommel. If the wielder speaks the name, the blade gives off a faint, cold glow, shedding dim light in a 10-foot radius until the wielder speaks the name again.</p>\n<h4 id=\"Development\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16.8px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"01c40e6d-cf60-4ce8-9ad2-016909c508f5\">Development</h4>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d3768670-edfe-4df7-8499-768d4f5e8f33\">It&rsquo;s only a matter of minutes before the Black Earth cultists in Red Larch &mdash; the so-called Bringers of Woe &mdash; hear about the characters&rsquo; exploration of the tomb. They don&rsquo;t want anyone to expose their manipulation of the town elders, so they slip into the tomb via the north tunnel in area T1 and hunt down the party. These cultists can catch up to the party here, or if you prefer, in area T9.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"54eb75a4-cbf0-4d42-90e6-70aca8a7971d\">If the party enters the dungeon before the sinkhole occurs, townsfolk or cult watchers near Mellikho Stoneworks or Waelvur&rsquo;s Wagonworks notice the characters&rsquo; activities. The cultists hurry to whichever entrance the characters didn&rsquo;t use and begin searching the tomb.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"33320f78-11f6-4b28-bffe-5b403e1217b4\">The Bringers of Woe are six&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Serif plural-monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #bc0f0f; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"223ea202-9ec9-4844-8dda-8e0fc2ac404b\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/bandit\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/16798-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">bandits</a></span>&nbsp;whose leather armor bears the symbol of the Black Earth cult. (This encounter is hard for a party that is only 1st level.) When the Bringers of Woe meet the adventurers, the bandits grimly and confidently say, &ldquo;We are the Bringers of Woe. We have come to reward your curiosity.&rdquo; The cultists then attack, fighting to the death. Three hang back and shoot at spellcasters, concentrating fire on one foe at a time. The other three advance to tie up the rest of the party in melee.</p>\n<h3 id=\"T8Approach\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"8e1f1698-6280-430c-9a87-45257c74a4f4\">T8. Approach</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7356ed5b-bfed-43e8-ba10-27c3255c5cc4\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d655178d-68bd-4d5f-b2b1-f659a225642c\">A passage &mdash; ten feet wide, ten feet high, and hewn out of the rock &mdash; runs forty feet ahead. A small lantern hangs from a hook in the wall next to the door at the east end of the passage. Sitting on a wooden stool by the lantern is a balding, beardless old male human in patched and faded work trousers and a matching tunic. He is idly whittling a stick.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5aca4bab-9886-44bd-a144-53c5ef73af7f\">The human is an elder of Red Larch named Baragustas Harbuckler, a retired carpenter (male Tethyrian human&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Serif plural-monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #bc0f0f; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"cf376b90-0d21-4650-987b-18e7603369e2\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/commoner\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/16829-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">commoner</a></span>).</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"12f14a36-7932-450d-83fa-8fa27bb917ec\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2e059b14-67cd-44a0-86b8-bd7a28e0b227\">Roleplaying Baragustas.&nbsp;</span>Baragustas, a Believer, is unarmed and afraid of the characters. He throws himself to the floor and begs for mercy. Baragustas is too weak to put up any sort of a fight, but he wrings his hands and begs the characters not to provoke &ldquo;the wrath of the Delvers&rdquo; by disturbing the stones of the tomb (area T9).</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"80ec131f-07be-4ee3-85fd-d6652ef771ab\">Baragustas knows everything that Braelen knows (see area T4). He freely acknowledges the existence of the Believers and explains the mystery of the moving stones, telling the characters, &ldquo;From time to time, the great stones change position when no one is watching. That is how they talk to us. They show us signs of coming danger and warn us when we make bad choices.&rdquo;</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"aa44e9ea-7c2d-44f8-a906-e75779289896\">The old carpenter knows much about the Believers&rsquo; influence in Red Larch over the years. The recent involvement with &ldquo;the earth priests&rdquo; who help them to understand the moving stones is something he idly mentions. He is quite intimidated by Larrakh, and more scared of the earth cultists than he is of the adventurers.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2695c510-e967-48b1-8398-6af9f2da8a88\">Baragustas isn&rsquo;t as innocent as he acts. He denies knowledge of murders or any other foul play, feigning surprise at the mention of evidence such as the corpses in area T5. The old man had no hand in such activities, but his denial is a lie. He knows of the murders.</p>\n<h4 id=\"Treasure\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16.8px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"248b9ab2-1e52-4011-8764-0bed96bba068\">Treasure</h4>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c95f722f-87c4-4184-ae52-00c02e12c2b4\">Baragustas has 25 cp and 19 sp on him. He also has a simple silver wedding band worth 10 gp.</p>\n<h3 id=\"T9ChamberofMovingStones\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"23122b06-44ab-4be3-8316-72ad376c2b29\">T9. Chamber of Moving Stones</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body-Last--to-apply-extra-space-\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"afc060d1-49c3-449b-97a7-27c5b83fe5be\">If the characters speak to Baragustas in area T8 or examine the door to this area, a&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/black-earth-priest\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17429-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Black Earth priest</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#BlackEarthCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1686a871-21fd-4f2c-a116-1a42b52d8a5c\">chapter 7</a>) named Larrakh hears them. If he does, he quickly sets down his lantern and hides. The following descriptive text assumes this is the case:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"be1c9066-16e5-4fd2-9ae2-53ed3ab7b926\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"be441624-2ef4-4c82-83d5-7433ffb21f0f\">An enormous chamber with a twenty-foot ceiling has been carved out of the rock here. A lighted lantern rests on the floor near the center of the room. An odd array of stone monoliths &mdash; some upright standing stones, and others arranged in three-stone arches &mdash; stand around the chamber. Six low stone slabs are set against the walls around the perimeter of the room. Each holds humanoid bones, dressed in scraps of tattered cloth and rusted iron.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"f0af419d-0241-41e7-80a9-a0726ecd4687\"><a class=\"ddb-lightbox-outer compendium-image-center\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; text-align: center; display: block;\" href=\"https://media-waterdeep.cursecdn.com/attachments/2/487/poa06-07.png\" data-lightbox=\"1\" data-title=\"\"><img class=\"ddb-lightbox-inner compendium-center-banner-img\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; vertical-align: middle; height: auto; border: 0px initial initial;\" src=\"https://media-waterdeep.cursecdn.com/attachments/thumbnails/2/487/850/583/poa06-07.png\" /></a></p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d36a3e56-67cc-45c9-aff3-1e1ee57a49b9\">Larrakh is hidden behind one of the larger stones. He spends almost all his time in this chamber, studying the old stones and experimenting with the magical floor. When he sees the characters, he lashes out at them with his magic.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"95915902-652c-4a77-9375-510065013552\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"8a69ad71-2dad-46e9-b840-538aa561dc03\">Roleplaying Larrakh.</span>&nbsp;Larrakh uses the stones in the chamber for cover, but he has no intention of fighting to the death. If this place has been discovered and he can&rsquo;t swiftly and easily eliminate the intruders, Larrakh tries to flee through a secret door (see below). He triggers a rock fall to cover his escape.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"fceab13d-5d67-42f2-88c0-a4bd306ed11c\">Larrakh is in disgrace among the Black Earth priesthood after bungling some earlier missions. He is determined to conquer Red Larch without violence by subverting and exploiting the Believers. Before the adventurers came along, he planned to ensnare the Believers with ever-darker acts of obedience and evil, then take over the town through his new servants.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"8af247af-8b34-45f4-a9b8-a3e5b859c08d\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5cb39f70-ab78-4038-8397-71e9c6876a0f\">Bringers of Woe.</span>&nbsp;If the characters didn&rsquo;t already fight the Bringers of Woe (see area T7), they fight them here instead. The Bringers show up late for the fight, arriving from area T8 or the secret door a few minutes after the party defeats Larrakh or he makes his escape.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9dd8dca7-bd57-411b-8cdb-b09c1ab6cd55\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"01c6caa8-9b1d-42d8-8a98-39159eae4871\">Bones.&nbsp;</span>Upon the stone slabs are the bones of human miners who discovered this chamber before Red Larch was founded. None of the skeletons are intact; each has a crushed limb, chest cavity, or head. The injuries are consistent with mining accidents. The Believers revere these skeletons, calling them &ldquo;the Delvers,&rdquo; and leave the bodies untouched.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c860076e-8734-4137-8e89-e8bf72e52a0c\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6bb224c3-d9fa-4bb6-bde7-c395238301d1\">Secret Door.</span>&nbsp;In the southeastern corner is a secret door that requires a successful DC 15 Wisdom (<a class=\"tooltip-hover skill-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/basic-rules/using-ability-scores#Perception\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/skills/14-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Perception</a>) check to find by noticing the unmortared stone outlining the door. It swivels on a central point, making a narrow opening to either side. The tunnel leads to a wooden shed in the yard behind Waelvur&rsquo;s Wagonworks (Red Larch, area 16).</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"606d51fb-d0c9-454f-a429-a19edc17754d\">The earth cultists use this passage to enter and exit the tomb, and the Believers have disguised it to keep away the curious. Farther in, the tunnel is partially blocked with dusty canvas, broken beams, and loose rock to make it look like it has collapsed. A Medium or smaller creature can carefully pick a way through the debris. If someone uses an action to yank out a shoring timber, the jumble does collapse. Then, a 10-foot section of the tunnel is buried in the heap, blocking passage. Removing the debris takes a few hours of work.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"af679329-6f18-4cbc-97c2-8a2165d427ed\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"15d312dd-38c8-4bf8-b5ae-a8452ddf031d\">Moving Stones.&nbsp;</span>This area was a large storage cellar and workshop carved out by the dwarves of Besilmer thousands of years ago. The dwarves left behind an odd array of pillars, threshold stones, lintels, and carved stone doors. Human miners from the ancient kingdom of Phalorm discovered the dwarven delving. The miners chose to bury their dead here. Until the Believers of Red Larch discovered it, the chamber was forgotten again.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6c0596f1-caec-4459-846d-fe23fc7cc6c2\">The dwarves enchanted the chamber floor to levitate stone in contact with it, so the floor&rsquo;s magic can be detected with&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"cd3f1f83-8e9d-409f-9389-db451ca0966d\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover spell-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/detect-magic\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/spells/2065-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">detect magic</a></span>&nbsp;(transmutation school). A moderate impact on the floor, such as a dropped object weighing at least 1 pound or a firm stamp of the foot, activates the levitation effect, which lasts for 1 minute. When the floor is active, the stones hover less than an inch off the floor, and they move with a light touch. Thus, minor earth tremors can cause the stones to move. Intruders, even beasts, can move stones about accidentally.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"055d4bfa-1f29-41fd-8e8a-220e9fe7a5a0\">The Believers have never figured out the magic, and none have seen the stones levitating. Larrakh and the Black Earth cultists discovered how the floor works. They have been amusing themselves by shifting the stones around and telling the Believers that the mysterious movements are fearsome signs of impending doom.</p>\n<h4 id=\"Treasure\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16.8px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6c061d0d-569a-4228-b6e2-6b2265f349e7\">Treasure</h4>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"37901dc3-aa8e-4b52-b578-f93aa5a51e2d\">Larrakh was part of the attack on the Mirabar delegation described in&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/secret-of-the-sumber-hills#TheMissingDelegation\" data-content-chunk-id=\"314de439-e833-4a3d-98c4-97d49d71e769\">chapter 3</a>. (News of the delegation&rsquo;s disappearance doesn&rsquo;t reach Red Larch until you are ready to carry on with the next part of the adventure.) He carries four Mirabar trade bars, each a foot-long spindle of iron, like two long, four-sided pyramids joined at the base. These bars are genuine, so they make a distinctive tone when struck. They are worth 5 gp each. Any character native to the North recognizes the city&rsquo;s distinctive currency.</p>\n<h3 id=\"Conclusion\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"fd884ea4-7d19-4d91-9061-c35637f5d0be\">Conclusion</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1f0b15f8-07fd-4552-970c-bf1ca53e49a8\">The aftermath of the discovery of the Tomb of Moving Stones depends on how the last few encounters played out, in particular the discovery of bodies in area T5. The corpses are those of murder victims.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"cd9ecc96-590e-42a8-8331-24484c2a3ab4\">If the characters didn&rsquo;t pay much attention to the bodies, then the remaining Believers are able to abscond with them and bury them elsewhere before Harburk finds them. Red Larch is scandalized, but it&rsquo;s a matter of secrets and lies, not murder and justice.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"37ed91f1-a6ad-4343-9851-0aab1184ac96\">If the characters expressed curiosity about the bodies, or if you deem it likely that Constable Harburk reached area T5 before Believers did, then matters grow more serious. Harburk quickly draws the correct conclusion that the Believers are the murderers. The constable launches a full-fledged investigation.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ba547463-5a1a-4a9a-b740-5e426d5ac180\">If he can, Harburk questions Grund and Baragustas. Grund didn&rsquo;t kill anyone or witness the murders, but admits to helping stash the corpses. He says Albaeri Mellikho and Ilmeth Waelvur oversaw the process. Baragustas is also innocent of any overt wrongdoing, so he&rsquo;s quick to confirm Grund&rsquo;s story and exonerate himself.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2a568437-967e-4043-ad81-9f981fed62c8\">Marlandro Gaelkur, Albaeri Mellikho, and Ilmeth Waelvur are the actual culprits. Mellikho maintains her innocence in the face of all evidence, blustering loudly. Waelvur breaks down and confesses his involvement, and he implicates Mellikho. Gaelkur plays it cool as long as he can, and tries flees town a few tendays later when it becomes clear Waelvur is about to implicate him as well. The murderers also tell of Larrakh&rsquo;s part in the scandal, and of their use of his magic dagger.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2d10c5ba-660e-412b-890d-94b46dc96a3d\">This drama plays out over the course of the next month, with some Believers fleeing the town and others disavowing any knowledge of the murders. It might be tempting for the characters to get involved, but they have the four elemental cults to contend with. Justice for the Believers can play out in the background during the characters&rsquo; next few visits to Red Larch.</p>"}
{"_id":"GC6VoCMfpDZnd0nt","name":"PoA Feathergale Spire","permission":{"default":0,"UGVR9scTfzwLsmWX":3},"folder":"","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<h2 id=\"FeathergaleSpire\" class=\"compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ca81679f-42d0-4cef-8096-13493a248c96\">Feathergale Spire</h2>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"dfb785be-cbbf-40ea-9341-64a0d32d290e\">In the Sighing Valley stands Feathergale Spire, the Haunted Keep inhabited by the Feathergale Society, Waterdhavian aerial-mount enthusiasts who have pretensions of nobility. They call themselves Feathergale Knights.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"3af0a199-95e2-4c80-8341-31aada6d21d9\">Secretly, the knights are dedicated to Yan-C-Bin. They occupied the keep when the air cult established itself in the dwarven ruins beneath the Sumber Hills. The knights serve the cult as lookouts, messengers, spies, and a first line of defense.</p>\n<h3 id=\"SpireApproach\" class=\"compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"3707427e-1637-491d-937c-cc7582905e86\">Spire Approach</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"11426115-59b6-49da-b957-61840fb59e53\">When the characters visit the area, use the unique environment and its weather to add atmosphere. During the day, azure sky encompasses the tower and gusty winds buffet it from all sides. The wind sighs through rock formations in the canyon. At night, the wind calms to a breeze, and light fog settles over the canyon. The spire then appears to float among the stars on a sea of clouds. The summits of the hills rise above the fog like islands in that sea.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"8476474d-b7bf-42cb-ba06-932f2593b1e9\">You can initially describe the keep as follows:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"3d51f91a-3dac-4349-9e42-7e670a5cde62\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"497567d5-5a2b-4a04-aabd-f5214b751e3a\">Feathergale Spire rises from a pillar of rock high into the air, the tallest point for miles. Built from white limestone and embellished in marble, the spire resembles a gleaming sword that pierces the sky.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Boxed-Text-Style_Boxed-Text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"a4d625b1-6cae-4346-a2dc-c6b4344183a7\">The gatehouse faces the opposite cliff, its drawbridge the only apparent point of entry. Tall, wide windows encompass the bottom level of the tower, absent only upon the gatehouse side.</p>\n<p class=\"Boxed-Text-Style_Boxed-Text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e914e7d9-9a57-4dce-a621-f7dec7e17e12\">A circle of open stalls rings the tower&rsquo;s foundation where it meets the rock. Above each stall, the sculpture of a hippogriff in flight leaps from the tower&rsquo;s base.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2c6d3d07-485b-4a89-b4b1-f98aadfb30db\">Beneath Feathergale Spire to the east, a wide gusty canyon yawns through the hills.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c8454dc3-048a-48c9-918d-900cb84b4e14\">A steep trail leads to the drawbridge over Feathergale Moat and to the keep&rsquo;s main entrance (area S2). Characters who approach along the floor of the canyon (the&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/pota/secret-of-the-sumber-hills#SighingValley\" data-content-chunk-id=\"33886dff-02f5-453b-8446-d3afe36b75b6\">Sighing Valley</a>, described later in this chapter) can scale the stone pillar on which the spire stands. It is 400 feet from the pillar&rsquo;s base to the lowest level of the spire (area S1), and each level of the spire is 20 feet higher than the level below it. Flying characters can enter the spire from the pinnacle or through one of the windows in the courtyard gardens.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"792a0cee-56c3-42c3-9bc6-e062c2daf581\">Two&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/feathergale-knight\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17420-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Feathergale knights</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5873669e-1454-4cde-88cf-d6b1dfbfee11\">chapter 7</a>) patrol the pinnacle (area S11) at all times, taking flight on&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/giant-vulture\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/16897-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">giant vultures</a>&nbsp;to meet attackers. One knight is stationed in the front hall (area S2) with two&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/howling-hatred-initiate\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17421-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Howling Hatred initiates</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"86018bd3-6c7a-4c7c-9183-3f6096dd573b\">chapter 7</a>). In daylight, the pinnacle knights have an excellent vantage point. They are likely to know of the characters&rsquo; approach long before the party arrives.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"acb97e3c-5c74-4487-a548-5ae4e94448f4\">The knights&rsquo; reaction depends on how the party chooses to enter the spire. Peaceful visitors who approach openly are welcome. Those who sneak in or assault the spire meet the full defenses of the keep.</p>\n<h3 id=\"SpireFeatures\" class=\"compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d85ea723-3b02-49d9-bd88-c789b00a2f04\">Spire Features</h3>\n<div class=\"compendium-image-container-right\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; float: right; margin-bottom: 19.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7f87bf6b-4e32-4457-a483-1e6fa7ee8059\">\n<div id=\"Map31FeathergaleSpire\" class=\"compendium-image-with-subtitle-center\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; text-align: center; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e50d1bab-db37-47b7-bf23-f284afd2fbfb\">\n<p class=\"compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 309.992px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"328e8122-d09c-44bf-b5b8-88b9d44b5290\"><a class=\"ddb-lightbox-outer compendium-image-right\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 10px; float: right; padding-left: 10px;\" href=\"https://media-waterdeep.cursecdn.com/attachments/2/454/03-01.jpg\" data-lightbox=\"1\" data-title=\"\"><img class=\"ddb-lightbox-inner\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; vertical-align: middle; height: auto; margin: 0px auto; display: block; border: 0px initial initial;\" src=\"https://media-waterdeep.cursecdn.com/attachments/thumbnails/2/454/300/761/03-01.jpg\" /></a></p>\n<h4 class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-image-subtitle\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9516a023-c5c8-4ef8-b374-76e68fa2f3a5\">Map 3.1: Feathergale Spire</h4>\n</div>\n<p class=\"compendium-image-view-player\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; display: flex; flex-direction: row; justify-content: center; align-items: baseline; width: 309.992px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"fa5abef7-7417-4a01-92ff-b6e974e42c3a\"><a class=\"ddb-lightbox-outer compendium-image-center\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; text-align: center; display: block;\" href=\"https://media-waterdeep.cursecdn.com/attachments/2/989/poa5.jpg\" data-lightbox=\"1\" data-title=\"\" data-content-chunk-id=\"b71a08a9-9634-4c36-8026-cecff2651834\">View Player Version</a></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"fce2fe1e-841d-46d7-a0f2-5ed9f6e42fca\">The refurbished spire has the following features. Any exceptions are noted in areas to which they apply.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ea64fa22-cb04-496c-b4d1-4ae579d9077b\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"a8626693-a34d-4dc7-bdd7-d8638c25b023\">Ceilings.</span>&nbsp;Ceilings are 18 feet high.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6e5877d8-c20c-40b2-b53a-e17b84279b7d\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"81fdce3e-7ebb-4736-b192-f141274aeb17\">Defenders.&nbsp;</span>The spire is described as it is when the characters arrive. At that time, four Feathergale Knights and their giant vulture mounts are away until that evening&rsquo;s feast (see the &ldquo;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/pota/secret-of-the-sumber-hills#KnightsQuest\" data-content-chunk-id=\"66939a2b-36e6-4112-a4c9-9d58eceb6145\">Knight&rsquo;s Quest</a>&rdquo; section).</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"00bc2f13-1d86-40d8-9338-613e22b0744b\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ada34278-733c-48f1-a583-671a0c60c495\">Doors.</span>&nbsp;Interior doors are made of wood banded with iron. Most have no locks but can be barred. It takes a successful DC 20 Strength check to break open a barred door.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"8277f2e4-261d-438b-9133-afb478184091\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c04ccbde-979f-4054-b9fe-06d69c977c7c\">Floors.</span>&nbsp;All floors are made of white stone.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"b95d1a47-bcea-4506-9be0-f30bf30568cb\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"f3eba7dd-e171-4756-b66b-382736eb5fa2\">Light.</span>&nbsp;Due to its many windows, Feathergale Spire is brightly lit during the day and dimly lit at night. With the reinforced shutters closed, the light becomes dim during the day and dark at night.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6be73d0f-3e58-4a68-84c3-f67de66fa2a9\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"52f87c65-5167-4373-946f-d8ddf22f622a\">Locks.&nbsp;</span>Any locks require thieves&rsquo; tools and a successful DC 15 Dexterity check to open.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"dd7795bd-126d-4afc-bd47-380c03fd5eea\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6212269c-a131-4138-b32a-62a7aa34fe2f\">Treasure.&nbsp;</span>Feathergale Knights keep their wealth locked in chests in their cells. Each knight also has 2d10 gp in mixed coinage and minor valuables.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"4460b081-5603-4439-ad41-50d681297258\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1ea29fc9-9731-4361-9665-f5bddaffbd05\">Windows.</span>&nbsp;Oversized windows on the ground level allow light and air to pass easily into the tower. They stand 3 feet from the ground and are 6 feet tall and 8 feet wide. Smaller windows, about half the size of the larger ones, are on levels 2 and 3. Shutters reinforced with iron bands permit the windows to be shut and barred. A barred window is like a barred door.</p>\n<h3 id=\"FeathergaleMoat\" class=\"compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: right; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c5002661-633f-4fce-aba4-fc20ed6967f5\">Feathergale Moat</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"35d0f626-02c3-4349-9c8b-e54e87b1ede0\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"b608b43a-3a7d-413e-a814-41fef39086ab\">A gap of twenty feet separates the ledge where the path ends from the closed drawbridge on Feathergale Spire. The space between the cliff&rsquo;s edge and the gatehouse drops several hundred feet to the bottom of the canyon. Near the ledge, a brass bell hangs from a wooden post.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6284f2ce-97c2-435a-98c1-792a33b9ab91\">At the bell&rsquo;s ring, a female human&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/feathergale-knight\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17420-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Feathergale knight</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"39506364-7815-40a0-98aa-62c43c8c447b\">chapter 7</a>) named Savra Belabranta opens a small window near the gate, welcomes the characters, and courteously asks what brings them here. Savra lowers the drawbridge to allow friendly visitors entry. If the characters accompany her, go to the &ldquo;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/pota/secret-of-the-sumber-hills#KnightsQuest\" data-content-chunk-id=\"61cd3452-fc51-4e7e-b22c-8f10d1c55b0e\">Knights&rsquo; Quest</a>&rdquo; section.</p>\n<h3 id=\"AreasoftheSpire\" class=\"compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"4909d031-0a0f-4bd2-bcc9-ae226a3ebab4\">Areas of the Spire</h3>\n<h3 id=\"S1StableLevel\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e3de985e-a70c-49bc-819f-d45bc3dbc850\">S1. Stable Level</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"f6aa63a7-e920-48bb-906d-d22ee2ced2a4\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"0ef74d97-5c7f-49f3-b199-7f758f530016\">A circular landing surrounds the central shaft of a spiral staircase. The landing is piled with supplies and bales of straw. Radiating from the landing are twelve stalls with straw-covered floors. A harness, riding crop, and saddle hang in each stall. Swinging wooden doors cap either end of each stall, one leading from the tower to the stall and the other from the stall to the open air.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"cc63a91a-1e54-482c-b8e9-e01496b38355\">The round room in the center of the spire serves as a storeroom. It is filled with supplies. Any gear from the&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7339f531-305f-4b07-9e00-c6d315273471\">Player&rsquo;s Handbook</span>&nbsp;you want the characters to have can be found here. The knights are willing to sell items at a ten percent markup.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"dd00f476-78e3-4baa-a8d8-09970c6914ca\">When the characters arrive, four&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/hippogriff\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/16924-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">hippogriffs</a>&nbsp;and two&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/giant-vulture\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/16897-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">giant vultures</a>&nbsp;occupy the stables, each in its own stall, and one&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/feathergale-knight\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17420-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Feathergale knight</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7f68af36-69cd-4c25-80cf-8c1884da3be4\">chapter 7</a>) stands watch and tends the creatures. The hippogriffs and vultures are aggressive toward strangers that enter their stalls unless a knight introduces the newcomers. Knight disguises can fool the creatures, but only at a distance.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d5ab58c7-7a4f-45b8-b79f-20e4d39a506e\">The latches on the stall doors are fastened at multiple points on each door, so it takes two actions to open each door.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S2FrontHall\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"b55ffa80-31ec-4158-89e0-da628db38bd6\">S2. Front Hall</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"a5727621-108f-46f5-905a-adfbc0054a34\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"38ad1aa4-720a-432e-a298-6340702d632d\">The entrance is a thirty-foot-long hall of white stone. At the opposite end of the hall are two twelve-foot-tall doors like those of the entry gate.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d18d88d3-684d-4efa-81af-f98f1c610d27\">An eagle carved from a massive timber hangs from the far side of the ceiling, suspended on strong chains. Slender wings of steel sweep close to its sides. Its head is also fashioned of steel.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d4745a3c-6284-4e2d-9a86-6fa13d63a8ca\">One&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/feathergale-knight\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17420-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Feathergale knight</a>&nbsp;(Savra when the characters first arrive) and two&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/howling-hatred-initiate\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17421-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Howling Hatred initiates</a>&nbsp;keep watch in the entry hall. See&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"97d0cee0-4207-445d-b836-09c68b484a4b\">chapter 7</a>&nbsp;for their statistics.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"7167a71f-41a5-4c36-9a74-86c971335818\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1c4c01a2-c333-43f5-94b5-416dc6f653e2\">Friendly Entry.&nbsp;</span>If Savra has allowed the characters in, she tells the characters that they have excellent timing. She invites them to join the knights&rsquo; feast this evening, commemorating the tenth year of the Feathergale Society. Savra leads the party through the tower to meet her captain, Thurl Merosska, in area S11.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"80af0832-e798-4c19-b4bf-1529e45f34ae\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"4483669f-911b-47f3-b3b8-96b8dae33b61\">The Eagle.</span>&nbsp;The eagle is a battering ram. If released using a lever near the doors to area S4, the ram attacks an area that starts at the doors to area S4, extending 30 feet along a 5-foot-wide path in the center of the hall.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"72fd2780-2b91-45ad-bb4c-ec9c993e836f\">Each creature in this area must succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw or take 3d6 bludgeoning damage. Those who fail the save by 5 or more are swept along with the ram, pushed out of the hall onto the drawbridge, and knocked&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover condition-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/basic-rules/appendix-a-conditions#Prone\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/conditions/12-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">prone</a>. The eagle resets when it swings back, locking back into place and resetting its activation lever.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S3WeaponsLocker\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"810426c9-ddc3-4b53-b79f-4a442c27f67e\">S3. Weapons Locker</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9ed0795d-d7e5-43f9-9fae-11c22f47c387\">The Feathergale knights stow weapons and armor here under lock and key. The weapon racks currently hold four longswords, four suits of scale mail, four shields, four helmets, four longbows, and four quivers of twenty arrows each.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S4CentralStairs\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"82a6a78e-f3d8-4ace-ad93-8053f41117b8\">S4. Central Stairs</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"b6205cc9-9d40-4cec-960d-d904066e59b7\">A single spiral stair runs through the tower&rsquo;s center, with landings at each floor. The stairs have a handrail along the outer edge.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S5InitiateDormitory\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"183cc9fe-28e1-431d-974a-bc52a65b7a82\">S5. Initiate Dormitory</h3>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"165c612e-deca-4bee-baec-89e79692af4f\">Howling Hatred initiates, priests, hurricanes, and skyweavers sleep in this room on four double bunks. Most cultists spend their days in other parts of the spire.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S6Kitchen\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e13d41cd-bf7e-4ac6-9279-d8a522e088fc\">S6. Kitchen</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"087059d0-65a8-4842-8d33-f100ab27615e\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"650ddc8d-0541-4e70-bcef-008332e906a6\">In this kitchen, sacks are heaped along the walls, and a small pile of vegetables is spread on a table. A huge, steaming cauldron stands at the center. Two wooden paddles and two knives hang on a rack next to a brick oven. Four wall shelves hold a dozen loaves of bread.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6d74cf3b-381a-4f5e-b620-2ac22f1c2473\">Four&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/howling-hatred-initiate\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17421-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Howling Hatred initiates</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"e076e47d-afd3-48dd-8689-84d0f39853b9\">chapter 7</a>) stand around the cauldron inhaling the steam wafting from it. The initiates are trying to &ldquo;inhale &mdash; and become &mdash; the steam.&rdquo; These cultists also serve as kitchen staff.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S7Solarium\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"204523aa-3c69-4c35-a423-0802503ede16\">S7. Solarium</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6359be97-0b15-4a2f-a083-1924bfd3e396\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2fdbdf77-c05a-4fd6-a5fd-ce5cf51707f0\">A bright room occupies the east quarter of this floor. Flowers and shrubs of many varieties grow in a labyrinth of planters. Spidery red and purple plants grow suspended in baskets in mid-air. Robed humans water the plants.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"194c2b0b-12c3-457c-b5c8-a82b7c7437d8\">Three&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/howling-hatred-initiate\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17421-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Howling Hatred initiates</a>&nbsp;and one&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/hurricane\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17423-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">hurricane</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"bad32c6b-ac44-443d-8faa-d43227d50b3e\">chapter 7</a>&nbsp;for both) tend to the plants, contemplate philosophy, or train in this room. .</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"85a19773-70db-4648-b3d0-60f492cc624e\">Several barrels of fresh water are located around the perimeter of the room.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S8GreatHall\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1318c510-a27e-4e73-b928-9d9b83cc129d\">S8. Great Hall</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"cb96eeff-dc84-4f0c-af26-3c78b09dad05\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5ebaa289-5747-4f9b-821d-ba6698b0f9fd\">This great hall spans half the diameter of the tower. Between the overlarge windows, tapestries depict scenes of gallant knights on flying hippogriffs, fighting dragons and jousting with one another among the clouds. High on the walls are the mounted heads of griffons, wyverns, owlbears, and manticores. A long, curved table set for a feast stretches between the hall&rsquo;s twin hearths.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9ea6d1f6-36bf-4506-af9e-73c0deb5da1e\">When the characters first arrive, two&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/feathergale-knight\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17420-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Feathergale knights</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"9868cc9d-e646-4578-8e53-f94daa72ac2c\">chapter 7</a>) who aren&rsquo;t occupied with other duties or rest are found here. At night, the tower&rsquo;s servants sleep here after the knights have retired for the evening.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S9KnightsCells\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"96019c36-6fd0-4a58-8419-be45525c23bb\">S9. Knights&rsquo; Cells</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ad621317-77ae-4447-9e72-2126213e0e0e\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"bbe575a1-ac8a-4daf-9162-33bafd452154\">This chamber contains two beds, a fireplace, a closet, two chests, and a small tapestry on the wall.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d3e37545-43e8-4886-b10b-6fce8b467315\">Each knight&rsquo;s chest contains valuables worth d100 gp, and a feathered cloak.</p>\n<h3 id=\"S10MerosskasApartment\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d44e7ebe-a0bc-4059-b2e0-28046636f4f3\">S10. Merosska&rsquo;s Apartment</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ee260d37-877d-4f3c-95ac-eb1d14f3ca67\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5d3e6ef7-d262-408c-9952-c52f376a357d\">This chamber contains a bed, a fireplace, a closet, a writing desk, a chest, and a small tapestry on the wall.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"fc22e0b2-a78b-43ed-8f76-fc40750ad229\">On the desk, in a cylindrical leather case, is a letter to Thurl Merosska from Aerisi Kalinoth, written by her minstrel Windharrow. It reads as follows:</p>\n<blockquote class=\"compendium-parchment-blockquote\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; position: relative; width: auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c726ddc1-a275-46cd-9886-5aa320e1d591\">\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body-Indented-Quote\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ddf8f6ea-2bb4-48ba-af8a-453fdb9aa918\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"b1c27937-f7c1-482b-a5cd-a371c0459bc6\">Merosska,</span></p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body-Indented-Quote\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1794b3ec-66c1-4068-98a9-66fe9b440896\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"00bcbe57-5db1-488b-bc3f-e3d61cd08798\">We are pleased to hear about the outcome of your altercation with the Black Earth cult, and we praise you for the capture of one of their prisoners. This noblewoman from Waterdeep has an interesting tale to tell, and we shall enjoy interrogating her further. Keep a close watch on the Sacred Stone Monastery. I want to know what our enemy is planning next.</span></p>\n<p class=\"compendium-blockquote-footer Core-Styles_Core-Body-Indented-Quote ParaOverride-1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px; text-align: right;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"6c7be3ff-00a8-4f08-8c08-7aec86a4811a\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"57f5770f-10be-4e8a-9a0e-153a5c929ff2\">Your beloved queen,</span></p>\n<p class=\"compendium-blockquote-footer Core-Styles_Core-Body-Indented-Quote ParaOverride-1\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px; text-align: right;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"90b86cb0-f406-4e2d-9575-7a55eb5c9b90\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2a3d7adc-891a-46ca-b7c0-a0b601b5a768\">Aerisi Kalinoth</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h4 id=\"Treasure\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16.8px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5c276849-b40b-46fa-bc64-93380a3f8fe8\">Treasure</h4>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"ffd01018-bfdf-491e-b6e0-79ab036f72f2\">In addition to clothing and personal effects, the chest contains 320 gp in a sack, a&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d0b9a140-2ee4-4425-9029-55a55bd8f3c0\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover magic-item-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/magic-items/potion-of-heroism\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/magic-items/4709-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">potion of heroism</a></span>, a scroll of&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"2c765841-d16e-4f98-8535-f7c7664b73ca\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover spell-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/beast-bond\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/spells/2370-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">beast bond</a></span>, and a scroll of&nbsp;<span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"77393c94-0d8a-43ee-b24c-7f6b84fe79c4\"><a class=\"tooltip-hover spell-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/skywrite\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/spells/2398-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">skywrite</a></span>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/appendix-b-spells\" data-content-chunk-id=\"98706e7e-dda9-4ca2-ab96-61b04fd59e6a\">appendix B</a>&nbsp;for descriptions of both spells).</p>\n<h3 id=\"S11Pinnacle\" class=\"quick-menu-exclude compendium-hr\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 19.5px; margin-bottom: 6.5px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"d633f677-c808-47dc-83b4-86032afb338f\">S11. Pinnacle</h3>\n<blockquote class=\"adventure-read-aloud-text\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-left: 0px; color: #242527; border-width: 0px 1px; border-top-style: initial; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: initial; background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; overflow: visible; text-overflow: ellipsis; border-radius: 0px; display: flex; position: relative; width: auto; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.6; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-style: normal; border-color: initial #e0dcdc initial #e0dcdc;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"43f42d2a-1bed-4802-aed6-1e3d4b83f53e\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"08a314b8-c87f-4f7f-b55a-8f10ac02ee3d\">At the apex of the tower, the stairs terminate at a round stone gazebo that continues upward in a needle-like minaret. Beyond this enclosure, a small lawn grows upon the top of the tower. Four paths paved with white stones point the directions of the compass, each path ending in a pointed stone crenellation. At the pinnacle&rsquo;s edge is a spyglass on a tripod, pointed downward.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 808.044px;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1adf6d31-bc2e-42d5-8934-0e996d7f736f\">From this vantage point, the Feathergale Knights possess a supreme view of all that transpires in the nearby canyon and the Sumber Hills beyond.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"92efd2e9-0018-4669-93f8-dd8304f7477c\">Two&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/feathergale-knight\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17420-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Feathergale knights</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"181b2b08-57f1-42b8-a48c-d0426950f9ac\">chapter 7</a>) and their&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/giant-vulture\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/16897-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">giant vultures</a>&nbsp;are stationed here. Every hour, one of them patrols the air around the spire. The other patrols the tower. They watch for danger and fellow knights sent on errands. When the characters first arrive at the spire,&nbsp;<a class=\"tooltip-hover monster-tooltip\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none; font-weight: bold !important;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/thurl-merosska\" data-tooltip-href=\"//www.dndbeyond.com/monsters/17425-tooltip?disable-webm=1&amp;disable-webm=1\">Thurl Merosska</a>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; color: #47d18c; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/adventures/pota/monsters-and-magic-items#HowlingHatredCultists\" data-content-chunk-id=\"a2cf7e35-dcd3-46e5-9bf1-34d275d2e565\">chapter 7</a>) is here as well, gazing west toward Red Larch.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"1e4c4a4a-3408-426b-9dc6-9c26d21d608d\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"c4d6f27c-c919-44c7-8441-65839acdd2e3\">Shrine to Elemental Evil.</span>&nbsp;Here in the high open air, the cultists gather to worship Yan-C-Bin. They sacrifice their enemies, first marking them with the sign of Yan-C-Bin and then throwing them off the pinnacle. In the Sighing Valley, area C2, scavengers swiftly remove evidence of the knights&rsquo; dark deeds.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 12px; width: 850.019px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #f9f9f9;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"5597adf1-2b7d-4d87-a074-46790382a8ab\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Bold-Italic-Serif\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\" data-content-chunk-id=\"bf201cd9-f961-40f1-baab-8f5be233d173\">Spyglass.&nbsp;</span>Those who gaze through the spyglass without moving it first see a hooded figure enter the concealed door in Knifepoint Gully (area V3).</p>"}
